def:- it is use to set the result-set in Ascending(ASE) / Decending(DESC).
Syntax:-
SELECT column1, column2, ...
FROM table_name
ORDER BY column1, column2, ... ASC|DESC;

Ex:-
SELECT * FROM Products
ORDER BY Price;

Ex:-
SELECT * FROM Products
ORDER BY Price DESC;

Ex:-Order Alphabetically
SELECT * FROM Products
ORDER BY ProductName;

Ex-Alphabetically dESCENDING
SELECT * FROM Products
ORDER BY ProductName DESC;

Ex:-ORDER BY Several Columns
SELECT * FROM Customers
ORDER BY Country, CustomerName;

Ex:-Using Both ASC and DESC
SELECT * FROM Customers
ORDER BY Country ASC, CustomerName DESC;
